data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. NO CDD! New Roof in 2021, A/C 2020, Water heater 2017, major systems are done! Completely fenced and USDA Eligible, FHA, VA welcome! Possible contribution to closing costs, buy-down or cosmetic upgrades with acceptable offer. 3/2 with large Office/flex space that could be 4th bedroom. Large corner lot in Myrtlewood, close to Hunt Fountain Park. One owner home that has been well cared for, curb appeal galore and pride of ownership shows! Large covered front porch looks out onto lovely landscaping. Entry closet for jackets (it does get cool in Florida!) Vaulted ceilings in the living room with ceiling fan and large sliders lead out to the lanai. Dining nook and kitchen have laminate flooring, lots of solid wood cabinets, closet pantry and breakfast bar. Split plan boasts a primary bedroom with dual walk in closets, double vanities and a step-in shower. Opposite side of the home you will find a large den with double doored entry, perfect for an office or a 4th bedroom. Common/guest bath and 2 more bedrooms, with loads of closet space. Both bathrooms have generous linen closets. Expansive, completely fenced backyard has Oversized utility shed that stays with the home. The patio is spacious with vaulted, insulated ceiling, fully screened and an extra large overhang/concrete pad to protect from the elements. Major systems are done, no issues with Home Insurance! Roof replaced in 2021, A/C in 2020, Bradford Electric hydrojet water heater in 2017. The garage door opening has an adjustable screen, keeping the bugs out on cool days. Quiet Cul-de-sac community close to shopping, schools, golf courses, parks & churches. Perfect first time home or anyone looking to downsize, this home has been lovingly cared for by the original owners.  Seller is motivated! Make an appointment to see it today!
